cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the registration of 3D human facial images, which involves computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of thin-plate spline (TPS) protocol, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of PCA-based feature recognition, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.MM) and the study of human trait diversity and disease genetics (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the method in forensics and high-throughput analysis of human facial feature variation, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
